381. The synonymous ad- jectives vetus and antiquos jointly express the idea cf ‘ old' with increased emphasis: the same occurs Most. 476, Persa 53, Mil. gl. 751, Poen. v 2, 18, Amph. prol. 118. The same phrase occurs in the writers of the silver age, e. g. Velleius Paterculus and Pliny the young- er: see also the commentators on Juv. VI 21.
